site/index.html:314:                Track <span class="gradient-text">Claude.ai</span> Usage
site/index.html:319:                Keep track of Claude.ai plan usage at a glance, with optional ChatGPT quota and Gemini status visibility when configured. A lightweight macOS menu bar app for power users.
site/index.html:330:                <a href="https://github.com/eddmann/Pinemeter" class="px-8 py-4 text-lg font-semibold text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 hover:text-slate-900 dark:hover:text-white transition-colors inline-flex items-center gap-3 border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-700 rounded-2xl hover:border-slate-300 dark:hover:border-slate-600 bg-white/50 dark:bg-slate-800/50 backdrop-blur">
site/index.html:354:                <p class="text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400 text-lg max-w-2xl mx-auto">Powerful features designed for Claude.ai power users who want complete visibility into Claude.ai usage, plus optional ChatGPT quota and Gemini status visibility.</p>
site/index.html:366:                    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3 text-slate-900 dark:text-white">Claude.ai Monitoring</h3>
site/index.html:367:                    <p class="text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">Track Claude.ai 5-hour session limits, 7-day weekly usage, and Sonnet-specific limits in real-time. Never get caught off guard by hitting your limits.</p>
site/index.html:400:                    <p class="text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">Automatic Claude.ai usage updates every 1, 5, or 10 minutes. Set it and forget it - your Claude.ai usage data is always up to date.</p>
site/index.html:411:                    <p class="text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">Export usage data as JSON for integration with external tools, scripts, and dashboards (e.g. Claude Code statusline).</p>
site/index.html:422:                    <p class="text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">Claude session keys, ChatGPT session cookies, and Gemini API keys are stored through macOS Keychain-backed boundaries. Diagnostics are sanitized and credentials never leave your machine.</p>
site/index.html:433:                <p class="text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400 text-lg max-w-3xl mx-auto">Start with Claude.ai monitoring, then add ChatGPT or Gemini when you want extra provider visibility.</p>
site/index.html:438:                    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3 text-slate-900 dark:text-white">Claude.ai</h3>
site/index.html:439:                    <p class="text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">Import a signed-in browser session or paste a Claude <code>sessionKey</code>/Cookie header. Pinemeter tracks 5-hour, weekly, and Sonnet usage windows.</p>
site/index.html:442:                    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3 text-slate-900 dark:text-white">ChatGPT</h3>
site/index.html:443:                    <p class="text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">Optional quota visibility uses a local browser session when configured. If ChatGPT is unavailable or rejected, Claude monitoring continues.</p>
site/index.html:446:                    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3 text-slate-900 dark:text-white">Gemini</h3>
site/index.html:447:                    <p class="text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">Optional Gemini status visibility uses an API key entered in Settings and stored in Keychain, with sanitized status diagnostics.</p>
site/index.html:462:                            <li>Claude session keys, ChatGPT session cookies, and Gemini API keys are stored locally through Keychain boundaries.</li>
site/index.html:471:                            <li>Settings exposes provider-specific repair, reconnect, and clear actions.</li>
site/index.html:472:                            <li>Unavailable, rejected, and rate-limited provider states show sanitized copyable errors without raw credentials.</li>
